<br>
The ogre follows the gnome around every waking moment.  Almost like a pet.  The gnome gets flustered with every little thing the ogre does, even though the ogre has the best intentions.  The gnome has a short temper while the ogre is a kind, honorable warrior.  The reason the ogre follows him around is the life debt he owes the gnome.<br>
<br>
The gnome saved the ogres life when he was but a young ogre, and the ogre has a sense of honor which tells him to follow and protect the gnome wherever he goes, although it's usually the cleric helping the ogre out of trouble. <br>
<br>
I love speaking like an ogre, and it's a challenge to stay in character with him 24/7.  Just something I'd like to do someday. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=siava>Siava</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.knology.net/~ahnmei/savepoint.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>No skills. No brains.<br> 
