<br>
But if time were unlimited and work didn't exist, I have a few characters in my mind, on other servers, and in the EQ RPG that I would love bring to life on FV and dedicate real time to.<br>
<br>
- Thanna Raindancer, druid of Karana (currently exists on Lanys T'Vyl)  Haven't really thought out a detailed story for her, it's just a nice change being a goodie and running around doing good deeds.  She loves the rain, sees it as a blessing of approval from Karana, and as her name suggests, dances around in the rain whenever possible.<br>
<br>
- Odeu, erudite necromancer (also on Lanys).  I wrote a bit of story for her for Ayrielle's story contest.  A seriously evil character  Unlike Didi who's evil in alignment but loyal and friendly to husband, guild, and other evils; Odeu is absolutely interested in herself alone.<br>
<br>
- Darlaan, high elf magician (playing in the EQ RPG).  Darlaan is a poor distant cousin of the Thex family and never lets anybody forget it.  He's the only son with 4 sisters, obsesses about his robes and appearance, and comes across, well, rather effeminate.  He's very amusing to play. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
- female paladin of Erollisi Marr.  This one doesn't exist anywhere because she'd need too much time.  But I'd love to start up a drop-dead gorgeous female paladin who'd run around wearing the sexiest armour she could find, doing good deeds and helping young folks.  She would be completely unaware of her appearance and dedicated to purity and chastity, and would remain happily single.  I'd probably make her a half-elf considering the armour graphics they get. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
- gnomish monk and gnomish druid, of course.  If I were rich enough to buy an endless supply of gnome illusion potions (or had a pet shaman) this would be very entertaining. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
